Reasoning: The paper discusses network design strategies and evaluates the effects of network coding, MAC, and multi-packet reception on network throughput. This falls under the category of computer networks and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses fairness allocation by the MAC, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a MAC that provides higher saturation throughput gains and fairness among flows, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the non-monotonic saturation behavior found in COPE experiments, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper provides an estimate of achievable gains for cross-layer design, which falls under the category of performance (cs.PF).
